<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="long-adv">long <strong><em>adv</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /lɒŋ/    美 /lɔːŋ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>长久地；长期地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Have you been <strong>waiting long</strong>? 
你等了很久了吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It wasn't long before</strong> (= soon) she had persuaded him.
没用多久她就把他说服了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He retired <strong>long before</strong> the war. 
他早在战争之前就退休了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2all">2.<strong>[常与all 连用] 在整个期间：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>all day</strong> / <strong>night long</strong>
整天/整夜</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="as-so-long-as">as / so long as</h3>
<p>1.<strong>只要：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don't mind where you go, as long as you're back before midnight.
只要你在午夜之前回来，你去哪儿都行。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 7</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One's life has value so long as one brings value to the life of others.
一个人只要给别人的生活带来价值，他的生命就是有价值的。</p><footer>2012 江苏改</footer></div>

<h3 id="before-long">before long</h3>
<p>1.<strong>很快；不久：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hope to hear from you before long. 
我希望不久就能收到你的信。</p></div>

<h3 id="for-so-long">for (so) long</h3>
<p>1.<strong>长久地；长时间地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Danny has worked hard for long to realize his dream.
为实现梦想，丹尼一直在努力工作。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sorry I haven't written for so long.
真抱歉，我好长时间没给你写信了。</p><footer>译林② – 2</footer></div>

<h3 id="no-longer-not-any-longer">no longer / not ... any longer</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不再：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He didn't smoke any longer after the operation.
动过手术后他不再抽烟了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>No longer has she kept in touch with us since she went abroad for further education. 
自从出国留学后，她就不再和我们保持联系了。</p><footer>2011 上海</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>According to a medical journal, runners live three years <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (long) than non-runners.  （2018 全国改）  </li>
<li>You won't find paper cutting difficult <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (只要) you keep practicing it.  （2015 北京改）<br />
A.even though<br />
B.as long as<br />
C.as if<br />
D.ever since  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. longer  2. as / so long as  </p></div>